theorem
Th35: (p is  first-col-of-circulant implies ( - p ) is  first-col-of-circulant)
proof
set n = ( len p );
assume p is  first-col-of-circulant;
then consider M1 being (Matrix of n,K) such that A1: M1 is_col_circulant_about p by CKB11:def 1;
set M2 = ( - M1 );
A2: ( Indices M1 ) = [: ( Seg n ),( Seg n ) :] by MATRIX_1:24;
A3: ( Indices ( - M1 ) ) = [: ( Seg n ),( Seg n ) :] by MATRIX_1:24;
p is (Element of ( ( len p ) -tuples_on (the carrier of K) )) by FINSEQ_2:92;
then A4: ( - p ) is (Element of ( ( len p ) -tuples_on (the carrier of K) )) by FINSEQ_2:113;
then A5: ( len ( - p ) ) = ( len p ) by CARD_1:def 7;
A6: ( dom p ) = ( Seg ( len p ) ) by FINSEQ_1:def 3;
A7: (for i,j being Nat holds ([ i,j ] in ( Indices ( - M1 ) ) implies ( ( - M1 ) * (i,j) ) = ( ( - p ) . ( ( ( i - j ) mod ( len ( - p ) ) ) + 1 ) )))
proof
let i being Nat,j being Nat;
assume A8: [ i,j ] in ( Indices ( - M1 ) );
then A9: ( ( ( i - j ) mod n ) + 1 ) in ( Seg n ) by A3,CKB3:1;
( ( - M1 ) * (i,j) ) = ( - ( M1 * (i,j) ) ) by A2,A3,A8,MATRIX_3:def 2
.= ( ( comp K ) . ( M1 * (i,j) ) ) by VECTSP_1:def 13
.= ( ( comp K ) . ( p . ( ( ( i - j ) mod ( len p ) ) + 1 ) ) ) by A1,A2,A3,A8,CKB9:def 1
.= ( ( - p ) . ( ( ( i - j ) mod ( len p ) ) + 1 ) ) by A6,A9,FUNCT_1:13;
hence thesis by A4,CARD_1:def 7;
end;
( len ( - M1 ) ) = n by MATRIX_1:24;
then M2 is_col_circulant_about ( - p ) by A5,A7,CKB9:def 1;
then consider M2 being (Matrix of ( len ( - p ) ),K) such that A10: M2 is_col_circulant_about ( - p ) by A5;
take M2;
thus thesis by A10;
end;
